# Arc: HollowWorld | Scene: TheHollowWorldWarrior6
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Another week had passed since Sarah had come upon the cave and the strange man."
    new "Another week had passed since Sarah had come upon the cave and the strange man."

    old "His words, the effects of the water, all of it had been hard for her to shake."
    new "His words, the effects of the water, all of it had been hard for her to shake."

    old "Samayra had by now become herself, if not more than herself."
    new "Samayra had by now become herself, if not more than herself."

    old "Where once she trudged along, struggling through the desert, unable to keep up, she now began and ended each day with a strange serenity."
    new "Where once she trudged along, struggling through the desert, unable to keep up, she now began and ended each day with a strange serenity."

    old "Exhaustion. Disease. The dirt of the desert."
    new "Exhaustion. Disease. The dirt of the desert."

    old "None of it seemed to be able to take hold of her anymore."
    new "None of it seemed to be able to take hold of her anymore."

    old "Instead, she now marched along with the others, and when they put down their gear at the end of the day, nearing collapse, she simply sat down as though it meant nothing."
    new "Instead, she now marched along with the others, and when they put down their gear at the end of the day, nearing collapse, she simply sat down as though it meant nothing."

    old "The water had driven out the sickness, but so too did it keep all other decay at bay."
    new "The water had driven out the sickness, but so too did it keep all other decay at bay."

    old "To see the girl, so frail and lithe of body, now so resilient, Sarah could offer no rational explanation."
    new "To see the girl, so frail and lithe of body, now so resilient, Sarah could offer no rational explanation."

    old "As the thoughts of the encounter continued to swirl through Sarah's mind, she had for a moment lost sight of the situation around her."
    new "As the thoughts of the encounter continued to swirl through Sarah's mind, she had for a moment lost sight of the situation around her."

    old "Only in the last few days had she managed to focus on her work again."
    new "Only in the last few days had she managed to focus on her work again."

    old "But by the time Sarah had done so, she had found the mercenary company in dire straits."
    new "But by the time Sarah had done so, she had found the mercenary company in dire straits."

    old "Food had begun to run low, forcing them to impose even stricter ration policies."
    new "Food had begun to run low, forcing them to impose even stricter ration policies."

    old "Water too, had begun to run low, when it was found that one of the wagons had been torn open on a jagged rock, spilling the water into the thirsty desert sand."
    new "Water too, had begun to run low, when it was found that one of the wagons had been torn open on a jagged rock, spilling the water into the thirsty desert sand."

    old "The men had grown increasingly resentful, their wealth from Bagrad now cast away into the desert."
    new "The men had grown increasingly resentful, their wealth from Bagrad now cast away into the desert."

    old "Poor. Hungry. Thirsty."
    new "Poor. Hungry. Thirsty."

    old "Perhaps if they had been defeated in the battle, the men could have more easily carried their circumstance, but they had been victorious."
    new "Perhaps if they had been defeated in the battle, the men could have more easily carried their circumstance, but they had been victorious."

    old "Not that long ago, they had rejoiced as conquerors, and now they lived as beggars."
    new "Not that long ago, they had rejoiced as conquerors, and now they lived as beggars."

    old "With strict rations, even the soft reprieve of a day's march by the campfire had been cut short, robbed of drink to celebrate."
    new "With strict rations, even the soft reprieve of a day's march by the campfire had been cut short, robbed of drink to celebrate."

    old "And so, gathered around their campfires, the men of the mercenary company had only their grievances and their hatreds for company."
    new "And so, gathered around their campfires, the men of the mercenary company had only their grievances and their hatreds for company."

    old "And around the campfire, they exchanged them freely and eagerly."
    new "And around the campfire, they exchanged them freely and eagerly."

    old "They cursed many things, but as men are prone to do, they soon found a concensus for their hatreds."
    new "They cursed many things, but as men are prone to do, they soon found a concensus for their hatreds."

    old "The man who had crowned them with victory, the man who had taken it away from them."
    new "The man who had crowned them with victory, the man who had taken it away from them."

    old "Like children, the men of the camp could abide the gentle hand and the firm hand, but they could not tolerate the fickle hand."
    new "Like children, the men of the camp could abide the gentle hand and the firm hand, but they could not tolerate the fickle hand."

    old "So, their hatreds grew."
    new "So, their hatreds grew."

    old "It was on such a night, where Sarah could hear the men whisper among themselves, that she had been invited to Vaelen's tent."
    new "It was on such a night, where Sarah could hear the men whisper among themselves, that she had been invited to Vaelen's tent."

    old "Present already was Gideon, who along with Sarah was attributed most of the blame by Vaelen."
    new "Present already was Gideon, who along with Sarah was attributed most of the blame by Vaelen."

    old "For most worryingly of all, more so than their lack of food and lack of water, was a more grave fact."
    new "For most worryingly of all, more so than their lack of food and lack of water, was a more grave fact."

    old "The fact that by most estimates, they should have reached the city of Nauyziri by now."
    new "The fact that by most estimates, they should have reached the city of Nauyziri by now."

    old "They could have all shouldered a great deal, knowing that their trials might soon end, but by now, nobody could be certain if they would ever end at all."
    new "They could have all shouldered a great deal, knowing that their trials might soon end, but by now, nobody could be certain if they would ever end at all."

    old "Sarah saluted as she entered the tent."
    new "Sarah saluted as she entered the tent."

    old "Commander Vaelen."
    new "Commander Vaelen."

    old "He threw her a temporary glare."
    new "He threw her a temporary glare."

    old "You're here, finally. Give me the status on our supplies."
    new "You're here, finally. Give me the status on our supplies."

    old "Sarah glanced over towards Gideon, his eyes fixed to the ground. Apparently he had already received his share of berating."
    new "Sarah glanced over towards Gideon, his eyes fixed to the ground. Apparently he had already received his share of berating."

    old "We've handed down orders to further reduce rations, but the most recent reports seem to suggest these are not having much of an effect."
    new "We've handed down orders to further reduce rations, but the most recent reports seem to suggest these are not having much of an effect."

    old "Vaelen looked up from his desk."
    new "Vaelen looked up from his desk."

    old "How do you mean? How can the reduced rations have no effect?"
    new "How do you mean? How can the reduced rations have no effect?"

    old "The most likely cause is a further collapse of discipline."
    new "The most likely cause is a further collapse of discipline."

    old "We've begun to suspect that officers are refusing to carry out accurate supply counts, handing out more rations than instructed while fabricating their reports to us."
    new "We've begun to suspect that officers are refusing to carry out accurate supply counts, handing out more rations than instructed while fabricating their reports to us."

    old "Vaelen slammed his fist against the table."
    new "Vaelen slammed his fist against the table."

    old "Then have them whipped if that's what it takes."
    new "Then have them whipped if that's what it takes."

    old "We're in the middle of a desert. If we allow morale to breakdown here, it's all over."
    new "We're in the middle of a desert. If we allow morale to breakdown here, it's all over."

    old "I understand, but that's exactly what the officers are trying to do."
    new "I understand, but that's exactly what the officers are trying to do."

    old "Vaelen frowned."
    new "Vaelen frowned."

    old "How do you mean?"
    new "How do you mean?"

    old "They officers work most directly with their own units. They see their own men every day."
    new "They officers work most directly with their own units. They see their own men every day."

    old "They understand that morale is breaking down as a result of forced marches and increasingly strict rations."
    new "They understand that morale is breaking down as a result of forced marches and increasingly strict rations."

    old "They want to maintain good relations with their soldiers, so they break the rules and give out more than they should."
    new "They want to maintain good relations with their soldiers, so they break the rules and give out more than they should."

    old "We can snap the whip on them, force them to follow the new guidelines, but this won't increase morale. It is likely to the opposite."
    new "We can snap the whip on them, force them to follow the new guidelines, but this won't increase morale. It is likely to the opposite."

    old "The men are already close to starving, and not only that, we are still forcing them on long daily marches that require the opposite of rations. The men should be eating more than usual."
    new "The men are already close to starving, and not only that, we are still forcing them on long daily marches that require the opposite of rations. The men should be eating more than usual."

    old "Vaelen rubbed his temples."
    new "Vaelen rubbed his temples."

    old "And if we give them more, and we run out, we'll all starve out here."
    new "And if we give them more, and we run out, we'll all starve out here."

    old "That wouldn't have been a problem if we had reached our destination by now."
    new "That wouldn't have been a problem if we had reached our destination by now."

    old "Vaelen glared at her."
    new "Vaelen glared at her."

    old "You mean to suggest anything, Sarah?"
    new "You mean to suggest anything, Sarah?"

    old "No, commander, but the truth is that even by the most negative estimates...we should have arrived by now."
    new "No, commander, but the truth is that even by the most negative estimates...we should have arrived by now."

    old "Perhaps we have been marching off course....perhaps we have marched past the city...I don't know, but we should have come across it by now."
    new "Perhaps we have been marching off course....perhaps we have marched past the city...I don't know, but we should have come across it by now."

    old "That city...the Mythran army there, they are our only real way out of this mess."
    new "That city...the Mythran army there, they are our only real way out of this mess."

    old "Vaelen sighed."
    new "Vaelen sighed."

    old "Yes, I am aware."
    new "Yes, I am aware."

    old "But the map..."
    new "But the map..."

    old "Vaelen tapped the map on his desk."
    new "Vaelen tapped the map on his desk."

    old "We should reach it...soon."
    new "We should reach it...soon."

    old "How certain can we be?"
    new "How certain can we be?"

    old "Vaelen paused before answering."
    new "Vaelen paused before answering."

    old "It's...one...perhaps two weeks, at most."
    new "It's...one...perhaps two weeks, at most."

    old "Gideon suddenly looked up."
    new "Gideon suddenly looked up."

    old "That's not possible, commander."
    new "That's not possible, commander."

    old "Our food supplies are low, but with the recent disaster on our water cart, the water supplies are even lower."
    new "Our food supplies are low, but with the recent disaster on our water cart, the water supplies are even lower."

    old "We have days left of water, not weeks."
    new "We have days left of water, not weeks."

    old "Vaelen pointed his finger angrily towards Gideon."
    new "Vaelen pointed his finger angrily towards Gideon."

    old "Your job is to solve my problems, not regurgitate them back to me."
    new "Your job is to solve my problems, not regurgitate them back to me."

    old "You've handed down the orders, not see to it that they are enforced. By whatever means necessary."
    new "You've handed down the orders, not see to it that they are enforced. By whatever means necessary."

    old "Gideon saluted."
    new "Gideon saluted."

    old "Yes, commander."
    new "Yes, commander."

    old "He quickly turned and left the tent."
    new "He quickly turned and left the tent."

    old "You should know that he does his best, given the circumstances."
    new "You should know that he does his best, given the circumstances."

    old "Vaelen was hunched over his map, not bothering to even look at her."
    new "Vaelen was hunched over his map, not bothering to even look at her."

    old "He's a man, if he wants to complain about how I run things, he can talk to me myself. He doesn't need you to speak for him."
    new "He's a man, if he wants to complain about how I run things, he can talk to me myself. He doesn't need you to speak for him."

    old "Sarah watched as Vaelen stroked his chest, the bulge just under his shirt was where he kept the stone from Bagrad."
    new "Sarah watched as Vaelen stroked his chest, the bulge just under his shirt was where he kept the stone from Bagrad."

    old "Always touching it, obsessively."
    new "Always touching it, obsessively."

    old "You had best start paying attention to the world outside of your maps and reports."
    new "You had best start paying attention to the world outside of your maps and reports."

    old "This company is coming apart at the seams, and the only instruction you're able to hand down is to whip people until they do as you say."
    new "This company is coming apart at the seams, and the only instruction you're able to hand down is to whip people until they do as you say."

    old "You used to know what it took to lead, but ever since Bagrad you've become distracted."
    new "You used to know what it took to lead, but ever since Bagrad you've become distracted."

    old "Vaelen suddenly looked up."
    new "Vaelen suddenly looked up."

    old "Are you questioning my leadership as well now?"
    new "Are you questioning my leadership as well now?"

    old "Because there have been others before you, and there will be others after you if you continue this."
    new "Because there have been others before you, and there will be others after you if you continue this."

    old "This company is at the most critical moment in its existence."
    new "This company is at the most critical moment in its existence."

    old "We either come apart here and lose everything, or we hold on, just for a moment longer, and reach the other side of this desert."
    new "We either come apart here and lose everything, or we hold on, just for a moment longer, and reach the other side of this desert."

    old "And once we do, all these problems that people are making out to be so big, will fade away."
    new "And once we do, all these problems that people are making out to be so big, will fade away."

    old "Vaelen raised himself up."
    new "Vaelen raised himself up."

    old "Now, go out there, and find whatever way you need to get this company moving tomorrow, and the day after, until we get to our destination."
    new "Now, go out there, and find whatever way you need to get this company moving tomorrow, and the day after, until we get to our destination."

    old "Am I clear enough?"
    new "Am I clear enough?"

    old "Sarah knew there was no reasoning with him."
    new "Sarah knew there was no reasoning with him."

    old "She saluted."
    new "She saluted."

    old "Sarah turned and left the tent."
    new "Sarah turned and left the tent."

    old "As soon as she left, Sarah caught Gideon from the corner of her eyes, waiting for her."
    new "As soon as she left, Sarah caught Gideon from the corner of her eyes, waiting for her."

    old "Shouldn't you be doing as you were told?"
    new "Shouldn't you be doing as you were told?"

    old "About as much as you should be doing as you were told."
    new "About as much as you should be doing as you were told."

    old "Sarah smiled back at him."
    new "Sarah smiled back at him."

    old "Treason, Gideon, treason."
    new "Treason, Gideon, treason."

    old "Sure, mayba you're right. Let's go for a walk before I get the rope."
    new "Sure, mayba you're right. Let's go for a walk before I get the rope."

    old "Sarah could see he needed it. She nodded."
    new "Sarah could see he needed it. She nodded."

    old "Sure, let's walk."
    new "Sure, let's walk."

    old "For a short while, the two walked side by side in silence as they got further and further away from the camp."
    new "For a short while, the two walked side by side in silence as they got further and further away from the camp."

    old "Before long, they found themselves far enough to be certain they were alone."
    new "Before long, they found themselves far enough to be certain they were alone."

    old "Standing atop one of the many rolling dunes, Sarah could see out across the desert."
    new "Standing atop one of the many rolling dunes, Sarah could see out across the desert."

    old "No direction seemed to offer any hints of where their destination might lie."
    new "No direction seemed to offer any hints of where their destination might lie."

    old "Just endless desert, in each direction."
    new "Just endless desert, in each direction."

    old "A full moon draped the world in pale light, making the dunes appear as silver."
    new "A full moon draped the world in pale light, making the dunes appear as silver."

    old "So, what do we do?"
    new "So, what do we do?"

    old "Sarah didn't bother to look at him."
    new "Sarah didn't bother to look at him."

    old "Probably what he told us to do..."
    new "Probably what he told us to do..."

    old "Gideon kicked the sand."
    new "Gideon kicked the sand."

    old "This is bullshit."
    new "This is bullshit."

    old "If I press down on my men any harder, they're going to turn on me."
    new "If I press down on my men any harder, they're going to turn on me."

    old "Sarah kept looking out towards the horizon, hoping something might offer her an escape. But there was none."
    new "Sarah kept looking out towards the horizon, hoping something might offer her an escape. But there was none."

    old "He's lost it, don't tell me I'm the only one that sees it."
    new "He's lost it, don't tell me I'm the only one that sees it."

    old "You're not wrong, but he's still the one in charge of this company."
    new "You're not wrong, but he's still the one in charge of this company."

    old "Well, maybe that should change."
    new "Well, maybe that should change."

    old "Sarah quickly turned to face him."
    new "Sarah quickly turned to face him."

    old "Don't ever repeat that to anyone, do you understand?"
    new "Don't ever repeat that to anyone, do you understand?"

    old "Gideon shrugged."
    new "Gideon shrugged."

    old "I was just talking."
    new "I was just talking."

    old "Well, that's the kind of talk that gets you killed. And don't think he's not the kind of man to do it either."
    new "Well, that's the kind of talk that gets you killed. And don't think he's not the kind of man to do it either."

    old "There have been others over the years, too ambitious, too hungry, and they've all met the same fate."
    new "There have been others over the years, too ambitious, too hungry, and they've all met the same fate."

    old "Gideon sighed."
    new "Gideon sighed."

    old "So what?"
    new "So what?"

    old "Just keep marching till we die?"
    new "Just keep marching till we die?"

    old "What else do you suggest we do?"
    new "What else do you suggest we do?"

    old "Turning back now...we don't have the supplies to survive the trip back. Even if we did, we have no idea what would even be left of Bagrad."
    new "Turning back now...we don't have the supplies to survive the trip back. Even if we did, we have no idea what would even be left of Bagrad."

    old "The only chance we have is reaching Nauyziri. If there really is a Mythran outpost there...with food and water...we stand a chance."
    new "The only chance we have is reaching Nauyziri. If there really is a Mythran outpost there...with food and water...we stand a chance."

    old "And what if its all bullshit?"
    new "And what if its all bullshit?"

    old "What if nothing is out there?"
    new "What if nothing is out there?"

    old "Sarah studied the horizon again."
    new "Sarah studied the horizon again."

    old "I have to believe that there is. It's our only hope."
    new "I have to believe that there is. It's our only hope."

    old "Gideon laughed mirthlessly."
    new "Gideon laughed mirthlessly."

    old "So that's what it's all come down to. Hope and a prayer."
    new "So that's what it's all come down to. Hope and a prayer."

    old "Sarah turned back to face him."
    new "Sarah turned back to face him."

    old "I've had worse."
    new "I've had worse."

    old "He studied her face for a while."
    new "He studied her face for a while."

    old "I like to think that I have a good read on most people, but I'll be honest, I don't think I've ever figured you out."
    new "I like to think that I have a good read on most people, but I'll be honest, I don't think I've ever figured you out."

    old "Maybe you're not as clever as you think."
    new "Maybe you're not as clever as you think."

    old "That's definitely true."
    new "That's definitely true."

    old "But why are you so loyal to him?"
    new "But why are you so loyal to him?"

    old "Because when I met him, I was in a very bad place."
    new "Because when I met him, I was in a very bad place."

    old "And out of all the people in this world that sought to take advantage of me, he was the only that ever offered me a real chance."
    new "And out of all the people in this world that sought to take advantage of me, he was the only that ever offered me a real chance."

    old "Sarah paused as in her mind she drifted back to all those years ago."
    new "Sarah paused as in her mind she drifted back to all those years ago."

    old "I've known tough times, don't mean I'm indebted to any asshole that gives me a hand."
    new "I've known tough times, don't mean I'm indebted to any asshole that gives me a hand."

    old "It's different for you and me."
    new "It's different for you and me."

    old "How's that?"
    new "How's that?"

    old "I'm a woman."
    new "I'm a woman."

    old "You can say it shouldn't matter, but it does."
    new "You can say it shouldn't matter, but it does."

    old "When I ended up losing just about everything I ever had, I saw what this world thought of me."
    new "When I ended up losing just about everything I ever had, I saw what this world thought of me."

    old "I mean...really thought of me."
    new "I mean...really thought of me."

    old "Without my titles. My wealth. My status. All I was to them a body they could prey on."
    new "Without my titles. My wealth. My status. All I was to them a body they could prey on."

    old "Sarah looked at him intently."
    new "Sarah looked at him intently."

    old "Do you know what it's like to walk around a city and see every set of eyes prey on you?"
    new "Do you know what it's like to walk around a city and see every set of eyes prey on you?"

    old "Gideon looked back at her, unmoved."
    new "Gideon looked back at her, unmoved."

    old "Well, I never had all the things you lost to begin with, and instead of eyes preying on me, I had the opposite."
    new "Well, I never had all the things you lost to begin with, and instead of eyes preying on me, I had the opposite."

    old "Everywhere I went, people turned away from me like I was less than the shit on their shoes."
    new "Everywhere I went, people turned away from me like I was less than the shit on their shoes."

    old "Sarah could see Gideon return in his mind to his own demons."
    new "Sarah could see Gideon return in his mind to his own demons."

    old "Sure, you probably didn't have it very easy either."
    new "Sure, you probably didn't have it very easy either."

    old "But this world makes poor men soldiers, and poor women whores."
    new "But this world makes poor men soldiers, and poor women whores."

    old "You don't know how close I got to falling off the edge entirely, dissapearing into some pit never to come back out."
    new "You don't know how close I got to falling off the edge entirely, dissapearing into some pit never to come back out."

    old "If not for Vaelen, I don't want to think of were I would have ended up."
    new "If not for Vaelen, I don't want to think of were I would have ended up."

    old "So no, forgive me if I don't turn on him so easily."
    new "So no, forgive me if I don't turn on him so easily."

    old "Fine, forget I ever said anything."
    new "Fine, forget I ever said anything."

    old "I didn't mean to insult you, Gideon. It's just...we're so vulnerable out here."
    new "I didn't mean to insult you, Gideon. It's just...we're so vulnerable out here."

    old "If we break...just a little...we're all dead. Only if we stick together, only if we keep this company moving, do we even have a dream of getting out."
    new "If we break...just a little...we're all dead. Only if we stick together, only if we keep this company moving, do we even have a dream of getting out."

    old "For a moment, the two stood in silence."
    new "For a moment, the two stood in silence."

    old "We're really going to keep marching?"
    new "We're really going to keep marching?"

    old "It's our only chance, fucked as that might sound."
    new "It's our only chance, fucked as that might sound."

    old "And so, each of them returned to their men, and from commanders to officers to soldiers, the orders flowed."
    new "And so, each of them returned to their men, and from commanders to officers to soldiers, the orders flowed."

    old "Less food."
    new "Less food."

    old "Less water."
    new "Less water."

    old "Longer marches."
    new "Longer marches."

    old "And it was as Sarah had expected."
    new "And it was as Sarah had expected."

    old "All through the camp, the men grew angrier."
    new "All through the camp, the men grew angrier."

    old "So near were they to the breaking point that even the threat of punishment was soon abandoned, for they feared what would happen if they lashed one man and made a martyr of him."
    new "So near were they to the breaking point that even the threat of punishment was soon abandoned, for they feared what would happen if they lashed one man and made a martyr of him."

    old "And each day the sun rose up against them with its terrifying heat."
    new "And each day the sun rose up against them with its terrifying heat."

    old "And each day it fell down on them like a hammer."
    new "And each day it fell down on them like a hammer."

    old "As the sun pulled away beyond the horizon, nightmarish heat gave way to the kind of cold that crawled into a man's bones and never left."
    new "As the sun pulled away beyond the horizon, nightmarish heat gave way to the kind of cold that crawled into a man's bones and never left."

    old "The campfires had long ceased to be places of comfort, now only places were men exchanged their growing rage."
    new "The campfires had long ceased to be places of comfort, now only places were men exchanged their growing rage."

    old "It grew, with each passing day, it grew."
    new "It grew, with each passing day, it grew."

    old "The angers they kept in their hearts now flowed past their lips."
    new "The angers they kept in their hearts now flowed past their lips."

    old "What were once whispers, grew to a chorus of rage."
    new "What were once whispers, grew to a chorus of rage."

    old "And still they marched."
    new "And still they marched."

    old "Still, each day, they bore upon their shoulders the very thing that drove their fury."
    new "Still, each day, they bore upon their shoulders the very thing that drove their fury."

    old "The endless march."
    new "The endless march."

    old "Like flagellants, they drove themselves on by their own punishment."
    new "Like flagellants, they drove themselves on by their own punishment."

    old "Further, deeper into the desert, towards a destination that meant nothing to anyone but one man."
    new "Further, deeper into the desert, towards a destination that meant nothing to anyone but one man."

    old "The name that had turned in their mouth from veneration to a curse."
    new "The name that had turned in their mouth from veneration to a curse."

    old "Treason was spoken plainly, openly."
    new "Treason was spoken plainly, openly."

    old "Some men ran away, unable to stomach the growing fever pitch of madness, rather to die in solitude in the desert. A different madness taking hold of them."
    new "Some men ran away, unable to stomach the growing fever pitch of madness, rather to die in solitude in the desert. A different madness taking hold of them."

    old "Yet, on the men of the march went, each day another step."
    new "Yet, on the men of the march went, each day another step."

    old "Supplies dwindled."
    new "Supplies dwindled."

